## Create

```bash
# macOS/Linux
python3 -m venv .venv
# Windows
python -m venv .venv

```

## Activate

```bash
# macOS/Linux
source .venv/bin/activate
# Windows PowerShell
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
# Windows cmd
.\.venv\Scripts\activate.bat

```

## Check it’s active

- Your prompt shows `(.venv)`
- Run `which python` (Mac/Linux) or `where python` (Windows) — path should point inside `.venv`

## Install packages

```bash
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install numpy pandas

```

## Run your script

```bash
python main.py

```

## Save dependencies

```bash
pip freeze > requirements.txt

```

## Re-install later

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt

```

## Deactivate

```bash
deactivate

```

## VS Code shortcut

- Press **Ctrl+Shift+P → “Python: Select Interpreter” → pick `.venv`**
- The integrated terminal should auto-activate (`(.venv)` appears).
